Cascading

Selector Specificity
    The type selector has the lowest specificity weight and holds a point value of 0-0-1.
    The class selector has a medium specificity weight and holds a point value of 0-1-0.
    The ID selector has a high specificity weight and holds a point value of 1-0-0.

key selector - The selector farthest to the right, directly before the opening curly bracket
prequalifier - Any selector to the left of the key selector

CSS colors - sRGB - 4 primary ways to represent
    1.  keywords                -   black, silver, gray, white, maroon, red, purple, ...
    2.  hexadecimal notation    -   #ff6600 could also be written as #f60
                                -   0 equals black and f equals white
    3.  RGB                     -   rgb(255, 102, 0)
                                -   rgba(255, 102, 0, 0.5) for transparency
                                -   0 means transparent and 1 means opaque
    4.  HSL values              -   hue, saturation, and lightness
                                -   hsl(0, 100%, 25%)
                                -   hsla(0, 100%, 25%, .25) for transparency
https://kuler.adobe.com/
